Yes, you can add Maven Central directly in your POM without touching settings.xml. If your company Artifactory is blocking access or your settings.xml mirrors everything to your internal repo, Maven will never reach central unless you explicitly define it in your POM.

You can do this by adding a <repositories> section in your parent POM or the moduleâ€™s POM like this:

<repositories>
    <repository>
        <id>maven-central</id>
        <url>https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/</url>
        <releases>
            <enabled>true</enabled>
        </releases>
        <snapshots>
            <enabled>false</enabled>
        </snapshots>
    </repository>
</repositories>

<pluginRepositories>
    <pluginRepository>
        <id>maven-central-plugins</id>
        <url>https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/</url>
        <releases>
            <enabled>true</enabled>
        </releases>
        <snapshots>
            <enabled>false</enabled>
        </snapshots>
    </pluginRepository>
</pluginRepositories>

This ensures Maven can fetch plugins like maven-clean-plugin from Maven Central directly, bypassing your internal Artifactory mirror.

If you want, I can write a ready-to-use snippet that you can drop into your olkypay-core POM so all modules inherit it. This usually fixes the maven-clean-plugin resolution error. Do you want me to do that?